<a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/news_page.php?archive=true&step=45&menustr=060000000000">&gt;next articles</a><br /><span class="headers">February 27, 2003 - Spell Research</span>
<p>
With the launch of LoY, spell research combines began to be used for other tradeskill combines (tailoring). While I had always resisted tracking spell research on the site, due in part to various caster sites already containing the information, and in part from way too much on my plate already, I've decided to bend a little on this one. I will be tracking <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g83&menustr=080105000000">new spell research combines</a> that came out with the LoY expansion, and only those combines. For those of you doing the happy-dance over this news, make sure to <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=4456">stop by the boards and thank Earenhylle Erlkoenig</a> for compiling a master-list of the new spell combines. ;)</font> </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 08:49:09&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 26, 2003 - Patch Update</span>
<p>
Some new bugs were fixed today, more are slated for the next patch. The bazaar bug that was giving folks an error message when they tried to buy stacks of items from player-vendors appears to be fixed. I believe the cast time on the charged spirit shift potion has also been fixed. Scheduled for the next patch is the fix to the collapsible bearskin potion bag and the collapsible medicine bag, which currently are only working for the new LoY alchemy. Also in the works for the next patch is the fix so that the 5-dose version of some of the LoY potions works properly 

We've made good progress on narrowing down trivials on the new recipes, and it's been a pretty productive week already. Now, if I could just beat my bank space into submission and magically juggle all the trade supplies onto 3 mules across the 2 accounts without having to character hop a gazillion times ... </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 24, 2003 - Oh, Happy Day!!</span>
<p>
<table width="95%" border="0" cellpadding="5">
  <tr>
    <td><a href="http://www.gucomics.com"><img
      src="http://www.eqtraders.com/pics/gu_20030122.jpg" border="0" width="200"
      height="300"></a></td>
    <td>
      <p>While others might wax enthusiastic about frogloks as a playable race,
      new things to see, new mobs to kill, I suspect that the majority of
      tradeskillers are most excited about the doubling of their bank space. (I
      swear, even my mules have mules right now!) Of course, that's not to say
      that we're not eagerly awaiting the other bells and whistles that are in
      this new expansion, but the bank space thing tends to overshadow the rest.</p>
      <p>Once the servers are back up and folks have a chance to poke around,
      I'll update this spot with links to newly-found recipes.</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 17, 2003 - Less than a week to go!</span>
<p>
<p>That's right, folks, less than a week until the Legacy of Ykesha expansion goes live. As usual, you can expect things to be crazed around here once the day hits, as folks are scrambling all over the place finding new recipes, new drops, and cackling gleefully over the expanded bank space. I'll definitely be joining in the cackling for glee, in between gibbering as I try to do 30 different things at once. I'll try to get things up here on the main site, with links from the front page to the new recipes, as quickly as possible so that folks don't feel the need to hit the boards every 2 minutes for updates. ;)
<p>I'm also going to try to squeeze in some time, somehow this week, to get
another chunk of the ever-growing database ready before I have to stop to put
all my attention back into the boards and the main site for the flood of LoY
information. Yes, we're still working on the database; yes, it's going to be
very large and very comprehensive; no, we have no release date yet, but I hope
to have it into beta before I go to the Fan Faire at the end of March ... I
hope. {crosses fingers, toes and eyes}</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 07, 2003 - Evening Update</span>
<p>
<p>The trolls that were lugging along the cultural forge from Grobb to Neriak have
finally arrived at their destination, complied with local fire codes, and set up
the troll forge in Neriak's Foreign Quarter. Meanwhile, the frogs are settling
in nicely, and have industriously replaced all the stationary tradeskill
containers that were damaged during their claiming of Grobb with ones that are
more suited to their more diminutive statures.
<p>I suspect there will still be some changes to be seen, as both groups settle
into their new homes, but this will hopefully settle down some of the more ...
feisty ... tradeskillers a bit. ;) <i>(translation: Primal Scream has gotten a
bit overheated lately. Settle down in there and remember your manners! Just
because you're having a bad week and are upset is no need to ignore the "no
personal attacks" rule, and many of you seem to have forgotten that a) this
is "just a game", and b) there are real people with real feelings and
opinions behind those other personas. If you're THAT steamed about something,
take several steps back AND self-censor yourselves before we get fed up enough
to start doing more bannings, or temporarily close that forum until folks
remember common courtesy.)</i>
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 07, 2003 - Bad Froggies, Naughty Froggies!</span>
<p>
<p>It seems there is no end of troubles for the troll race right now. Not only have
they been kicked out of Grobb, and been forced to go bother the dark elves, but
along the way, they forgot to some very important items. (Trolls aren't known to
be the smartest of creatures, after all!) Among the things forgotten is their
cultural forge, which seems to have been uprooted from their old home, but which
hasn't yet shown up anywhere else. I expect it's going to take time for the dust
to settle, so, for now, things like the trade supplies listings for Grobb ... or
<a href="http://eqtraders.com/sources/source_zone_page.php?article=g89&menustr=110000000000&sz=1054">Gukta</a> ... or whatever
it's called today, are NOT going to be up-to-date. I'll make some temporary
pages as the weekend progresses, but I expect there will still be a lot of
changes incoming before things finally settle down.
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 08:50:31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 06, 2003 - Another Patch</span>
<p>
<p>This is another day with a variety of things of interest to tradeskillers. As
usual, I'll add my commentary after each item:
<blockquote>
  <p>- Many Planar Recipes can now be used in collapsible containers. Some
  Planar Tailoring can only be done in the Tanaan Loom as opposed to the Planar
  Sewing Kit. Nothing that was previously made in the Loom was added to the
  collapsible tailoring kit. Skills changed were Baking, Sewing, Jewel Craft,
  and Fletching. <i>(Wheee! This is definitely a happy change for those packrats
  who have invested in collapsible containers. For those wondering, the only
  thing I can think of that specifically requires the PoK loom are parts for the
  planar armor quests</i><br>
  - Added gnome cultural recipe book to Ak'Anon. <i>(Using clockwork armor as a
  base, these are <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=140&rsa=Tinkering&sub=armor&sb=item&menustr=080120040000">tinkered
  armors with some brewing and imbuing required</a>.)</i><br>
  - Changed the weights on Spiritstones to be more in line with Faithstones. <i>(Spiritstones
  were changed from weight 20.0 to weight 0.1 to match the weights on the cleric
  faithstones. Additionally, ogre and troll shammies, please note that the
  Spiritstone of Innothule is now Spiritstone of the Banished, and it ports you
  to Nektulos, not Innothule. We expect to see the storyline explanation for
  this change "soon")</i><br>
  - Changed Collapsible Jeweler's Kit to 6 slots from 4. <i>(The planar
  jeweller's kit has 6 slots, so this is just fixing it to match)</i><br>
  </p>
</blockquote>
<p>Additionally:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>- Fixed a bug that caused merchants to charge a little extra or less (1
  copper).<i> (We've long known that vendors do creative rounding when you're
  buying multiples of items. I suspect that this might fix that.)</i><br>
  </p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'll likely have further updates to this later in the day, once I am more
caffeinated.
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 08:52:02&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 04, 2003 - Woohoo (updated)</span>
<p>
<p>Today's patch has many lovely little tidbits for tradeskillers, especially
shaman alchemists. My comments are in italics after the various items:
<blockquote>
  <p>- Added new potions for Vah Shir Shaman (and all other Shaman): Shadeweaver
  Portal. - <i>recipe has been found, and is <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=31&rsa=Alchemy&sb=item&sub=potion&menustr=080010010000">up
  on the site</a></i><br>
  - Renamed one of two items called Figwort. The Figwort sold in Shar Vahl has
  been renamed Ground Figwort to reduce confusion. - <i>the Gulon's Impunity
  alchemy potion will now use ground figwort</i><br>
  - Renamed one of two items called Drachling Silk. The Drachling Silk that was
  once no drop is now tradable and named Drachnid Silk. - <i>these are two
  Kunark forages that have been annoying due to having the same name. They're
  currently still only vendor-fodder, but at least they have unique names!</i><br>
  - Adventurers have learned new techniques for fighting Cyclopes. These great
  beasts are now much more likely to have their eye intact when killed. - <i>this
  should allow shammies to now make the Assailing alchemy potion</i><br>
  - Fixed the recipe for the potion "Soul of Incorporeal" to use a
  "feather". <i>- finally, a use for foraged feathers!!</i><br>
  - Fixed the recipe for the potion "Troll's Essence". <i>- it's been
  broken forever, but this old alchemy potions should actually work!</i><br>
  - Fixed the cast time on any 5 and 10 dose potions that were inconsistent with
  their single dose versions - <i>several of the potions listed as "Luclin
  potions" on our alchemy recipes page had a cast time of 30.0 for the
  charged versions, but lower cast times for the singles. The charged versions
  should now have the lesser cast times of their single-dose kin</i><br>
  - General Bragmur in Iceclad should now avoid ice flows that he was having a
  problem crossing in the past. - <i>8th shawl questers, rejoice! If the silly
  little General can remember his new route, he should no longer get stuck under
  the ice floes and lose his way!</i><br>
  - Terrorantula Silk, Feather, branch of sylvan oak, branch of planar oak,
  Drachnid Silk, and Drachling Silk are now stackable. - <i>erudite tailors,
  wood elven fletchers, folks making blessed fishing poles and others should be
  happy with this. If folks can post verification of these, I'll update the
  database accordingly</i><br>
  - Silicorrosive Grease is now tradable and stackable. -<i> tinkers rejoice!
  Since this little item is not only used in a quest, but in two other recipes,
  it's been impossible for younger gnomes to get access to this.</i><br>
  - Potions Aquatic Haunt and Serpents Drink no longer require reagents. <i>-
  potions that don't use reagents are happy things!</i><br>
  - Grandmaster Alchemist will now have a way to prove their ability. - <i><a href="http://eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=7484&menustr=035000000000">Grandmaster's
  Medicine Bag</a> has been made! Many thanks to Frizznik for convincing Jolum
  to give up information that he's temporarily forgotten - Thursday's patch
  should see the hail text in place on the live servers, as well as the ammo
  slot added to the trophy itself.</i></p>
</blockquote>
<p>With so many of these changes being related to alchemy, it would likely be
good to dive into the old Letters of Jonas alchemy books, and see how they have
been changed/updated to reflect this information. My many thanks to Verdandi for
putting together a "laundry list" of things outright broken/bugged
with alchemy, as it looks like it's helped pinpoint, and address, several
outstanding problems. <i>(My thanks also go to the folks who put in these fixes
as it's a good step in the right direction at addressing several nigglies).</i>
/bounce!
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 08:54:15&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">January 24, 2003 - Feeling crabby!</span>
<p>
<p>I have good news and bad news, and it's a very crabby day.
<p>On the good news front, those industrious tinkers over at <a href="http://www.tinkering.org">Tinkering.org</a>
have found the recipe for a <a href="http://eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=6490&menustr=035000000000">crab
cracker</a>, which is required for one of the currently-unsolved <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=149&rsa=Baking&sub=pop&sb=item&menustr=080020060000">PoP
baking recipes</a>.
<p>On the bad news front, the message boards are also feeling a bit crabby, and
are NOT behaving, in the least. The fix that was put in place yesterday morning
did not fix the problem, and we're still crossing our fingers that someone over
at the phpBB support forums will have some insights into exactly what's going
awry. I suspect I'll have several more grey hairs interspersed with the red
before all this is sorted out, and I know it's frustrating for our very active
message board community as well. The problems last week with the boards turned
out to be due to some other site running on the same machine as our message
boards, but this time it's something awry with our software or the message board
databse. ... bleargh!!
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 08:56:16&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">January 16, 2003 - </span>
<p>
<p>I'd like to apologize for all the problems folks are seeing with the message
boards recently. We're <i><b>still</b></i> trying to find out if it is a problem
with the software (I doubt many have tested phpBB under the massive load we
present it with), or if it's a problem with the server software or the new
hardware. (The boards were very recently moved to yet another machine.) I'm more
than ready to pull my hair out over it, and I'm sure some of you are as well. As
we find out more, we'll keep you posted, and we're trying to work on getting
some <i>stable</i> boards for folks to use.
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">January 09, 2003 - Patch Day</span>
<p>
<p>As usual, it will take a while to see how much impact this patch has on the
tradeskill community.The only tradeskill-related item that was noted in this
patch was a change in the effects on some of the <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=q138&menustr=120055000000#plateornate">quested
planar armor pieces</a>. I'll likely have more updates to this later today.
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 08:58:15&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
