<p><span class="headers">January 01, 2003 - Hoppy Gnu Ears!</span>
<p>
<p>Well, for some of you, New Year's Day is over, and for others of us, it's got
another 3 hours to go before it is over and done. Regardless of where you are,
best wishes from my household for a safe and Happy New Year! As a belated
holiday gift, I offer up a new recipe page upon the site, thanks in large part
to the recipe contributions from our community, and the compilation efforts of
Tebyen Trueheart. We're pleased to introduce a <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g100">real
life recipes page</a>, with some of our favorite meals, munchies, raiding
supplies, and so forth. Bon appetit!
<p>Addendum: Information on <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=q24&menustr=120055000000">the
Zek-bane weapon quest</a> is now available!
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 09:02:34&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">December 25, 2002 - </span>
<p>
<blockquote>
  <p>Twas the night of Christmas, and all through the house,<br>
  many creatures were stirring, even the (catnip) mouse!<br>
  The database gnomes were taking a nap,<br>
  but a site elf seems to have stolen Mum's (thinking) cap!</p>
</blockquote>
<p>... All right, so it doesn't scan well, but at least it is some
acknowledgement that the holiday season is in full swing. Whether your main
holiday was over days ago, or if that day of days is just finishing ... whether
you celebrate New Year's in a week, or whether your new year follows a Chinese
calendar, you're likely around a lot of folks that are celebrating <i>something</i>
right now. So, I have to be properly mom-ish right now, and say a few things:
<ul>
  <li>May your holiday season be a safe and joyous one. Regardless of the
    stresses of everyday life, remember to take time now and then to savor the
    company of those around you.
  <li>Remember there are real people behind those characters you run into
    in-game. Just because the game isn't "real life", don't forget
    that the people behind those players are very real, and your in-game actions
    have the chance to hurt, or help, other people.
  <li>Remember that practicing real-life alcohol tolerance and driving don't
    mix. Remember that others may/will forget this fact, and be extra careful
    when traveling. Generally, those irresponsible in their partying seem more
    likely to hurt innocents than they are to hurt themselves.
  <li>Remember, there is no "rez plz" in real life.
  <li>Remember to take time out to just plain have fun now and then. It helps
    you keep perspective.
  <li>Remember that random acts of kindness <i>DO</i> come back to surprise you
    now and then; so, whether in-game or out, surprising someone "just
    because" with a kind word, an ambush buffing, etc. really <i>does</i>
    make an impact, even if you don't see the direct result of it.
  <li>Remember that compliments cost nothing, and that criticism can do more
    damage than expected. So when your group actually manages to survive when
    something goes badly wrong, throwing in comments about what was done <i>right</i>
    can help ease the blow of the inevitable commentary about what was done
    wrong. This, of course, applies to the real world as well, but after having
    someone in a pick up group last night actually making an effort to praise
    stellar crowd control, it rememinded me that too often we're silent when
    things go right, and very noisy when things go wrong.
  <li>Remember to pamper yourself now and then. If <i>you</i> can't expend the
    effort to spoil yourself, why should you expect that anyone else will
    either?
  <li>Remember that laughter cures much. Tickle those corpses back to life,
    don't just click 'em! ;)</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">December 19, 2002 - Patch Day</span>
<p>
<p>The only thing in the patch message that impacts the site is the change to <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=q138&menustr=120055000000#plateornate">quested
PoP planar armor sets</a>. As we're still working on getting the updated
stats from the player-made <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=130&rsa=Smithing&sb=item&sub=pchain&menustr=080100160000">Chain Smithed</a>, <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=131&rsa=Smithing&sb=item&sub=pplate&menustr=080100180000">Plate Smithed</a>
and <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=137&rsa=Tailoring&sb=item&sub=plthr&menustr=080110160000">Leather Tailored</a>, <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=138&rsa=Tailoring&sb=item&sub=pslk&menustr=080110180000">Silk Tailored</a>
armor that was changed last week, I expect it will take time for us to be given
the new information and get it onto the site as well.
<p>There also seems to be a DNS problem right now for reaching the message
boards. We just got home to find the problem, and we're still trying to figure
out where the problem lies, since the boards themselves are up. For those of you
who are true message board addicts, you can try using <a href="http://mboards.racknine.net/phpBB2/">http://mboards.racknine.net/phpBB2/</a>
in order to reach the message boards. <i>However, be aware that your cookies may
not work properly, and so you may not be able to properly login to post.</i>
</p>
<p>
