		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 09:21:07&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">December 12, 2002 - Patch Day (updated)</span>
<p>
<p>As usual, it will take a bit before we're positive what impact the patch will
have on tradeskillers. It is also going to take a while before it all makes it
onto the site. So far, what's been confirmed:
<ul>
  <li>negative stats on some of the alchemy potions have been removed. More
    details should go up on the alchemy recipes page later today, after we can
    go through the list and double-check them
  <li>gnomish fireworks have had their particle effects changed. The folks over
    at <a href="http://www.tinkering.org">http://www.tinkering.org</a> have
    screen shots
  <li>the level restriction on <a href="http://eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=6302">anizok's
    gauze press</a> has been removed
  <li>the mana costs on the various enchanter-made mana vials have been cut in
    half. The FAQ on the boards has been changed to list the new mana costs
  <li>At least a couple of the PoP tradeskill armor sets (<a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=130&rsa=Smithing&sb=item&sub=pchain&menustr=080100160000">PoP Chain Smithed</a>, <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=131&rsa=Smithing&sb=item&sub=pplate&menustr=080100180000">PoP Plate Smithed</a>
    and <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=137&rsa=Tailoring&sb=item&sub=plthr&menustr=080110160000">PoP Tailored Leather</a>, <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=138&rsa=Tailoring&sb=item&sub=pslk&menustr=080110180000">PoP Tailored Silk</a>)
    have undergone a flipflop from INT to WIS and WIS to INT to better suit the
    classes that can wear the armor. It will take time to confirm that the
    changes were done across the board, as we hunt down folks that own pieces of
    these armor sets. As we receive updates, the <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=q138&menustr=120055000000#plateornate">PoP
    armor stats page</a> will be updated.
  <li>trivials on <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=140&rsa=Tinkering&sub=armor&sb=item&menustr=080120040000">clockwork
    watchman armor</a> changed. It will take a while before we're able to narrow
    down the new trivials, but the trivials have been lowered
  <li>I've been told that trivials on some of the fishing lures have changed,
    but as yet, I have no details</li>
</ul>
<p>Random updates to this list will continue throughout the day, as I hear back
from various folks regarding stat changes, etc.
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 09:26:14&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">December 09, 2002 - More about the boards</span>
<p>
<p>Whee. It seems like the code tweak needed so that phpbb properly tracks what
you've really read, and what you haven't read, was never stress tested with the
sort of load that we see on a regular basis, nor for the sheer number of boards
that we have. So, yes, things are beyond sludged right now, and I apologize for
that. We have a couple options from this point, and we'll be looking at those
alternatives carefully over the next day or two. One alternative would be to
back out the tweak that uses the proper "read" indexing, and go back
to it using your last visited timestamp to determine what you may/may not have
read. I don't really like that alternative, personally, as I like to process
posts from the boards in manageable chunks. The second alternative is to get rid
of the Marketplace forums. This would <i>more</i> than halve the hits to the
database as the main forum listing was generated, given the sheer number of
servers there are these days. I really don't like that one, either, but it may
be something we need to consider. Another alternative, which opens up issues
with seeing if one registered user list can be shared between two separate
message boards, is to make the Marketplace a separate message board.
<p>We'll let you know what we manage to work out so that we're back to the very
fast new boards once again
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">December 06, 2002 - bleargh</span>
<p>
<p>Some days, I just can't win.I posted here this morning in between errands
regarding the message boards spazzing out, and the moment I posted the message
and left for another 4 hours of nearly-fruitless running errands, etc., they
started working again. Anyway, nothing to see here, move along now.
</p>
