<p><span class="headers">December 05, 2002 - Mini Patch</span>
<p>
<p>Last night's patch fixed the issue with Froststone faction. Those who kill
those foul snow orcs should now be properly rewarded with a more positive
welcome from the Froststone dwarves in Crystal Caverns.
<p>I'm also busy right now changing message board links all over the place to
point to the new boards. <i>(I'll drop a post in the new boards with the URL for
the old boards, if you want to recover information from there, but I'm starting
to turn off posting rights to the various old forums, as folks are still adding
fresh posts in the Marketplace, etc.)</i> Please <b>DO</b> let me know if you
find message board links from the main site not working properly later today.

</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">December 04, 2002 - Patch Day, and more about the boards</span>
<p>
<p>Today has been a "quiet" day with respect to tradeskills and the
patch. There are a couple things to mention, however. A couple (or more, we're
still waiting on reports regarding the others) of the PoP pottery items have had
a recommended level flag added to them, as well as the addition of being
range-wieldable (woohoo!) There also may be an issue with faction in Crystal
Caverns. Those cantankerous dwarves in there can't seem to make up their minds,
and while they REALLY dislike all those annoying orcs in "their"
caverns, killing the orcs themselves now results in <i>negative</i> faction with
the Froststone dwarves. I suspect this will be fixed relatively quickly.
<p>We would like to thank everyone for your patience and tremendous support as
we made the switch to the new message boards. It's still going to be a bit
awkward until the dust settles some more and we can get past the glaring issues
to fine tune the less critical settings (in between keeping up with the flow of
new information for the site!) Your patience and continued cooperation are much
appreciated! In the end, all the effort should be well worth being able to host
the community far more economically.
<p>That said, we would like to offer our thanks to the folks at EZBoards for
their hosting of our message board community for close to three years. While the
time has come for us to move on, EZBoards were the home where our community grew
and thrived, up to this point. They still have much to offer communities that
may not have the time, interest, or technical know-how to create and host their
own boards. <i>(As well as for those communities, such as my server's boards,
where folks seem more willing to put up with popups than they are to contribute
cash to support the boards.)</i> We hope that the Everquest community does not
see our change of venue as an indication that we are in any way dissatisfied
with the quality of their services - we'd just rather spend more of our own time
and effort, and less of our cash! Thank you and fond farewells, Vanchau and
crew!
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">December 03, 2002 - Message Boards and More</span>
<p>
<p>With the chaos that has abounded IRL due to PoP launch, the Fan Faire, the
grand opening of the House Ogre's comics and gaming shop (last Friday!), my
strep throat and whiplash, I've delayed on this annoucement until the last
minute, as I needed some breathing time before doing final tweaks to the [<a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/index.php">new
message board</a>]. You ask, 'What new message board?'
<p>Many of you likely remember us mentioning our desire to explore other message
board options, after we saw how much renewal for our EZBoard Gold membership was
going to cost. We had a lot of folks approach us with different alternatives,
including the folks at Mazevo, and the EZBoard folks also worked hard to come up
with a more viable option for us. Fortunately, we had enough in the Community
Chest to extend the board Gold status to cover the PoP launch chaos, but that
extension is about to expire. After a lot of deliberation and price comparisons,
and our very strong desire to keep the boards and site as ad free as possible,
we've decided to host the boards with our site hosting provider, and run phpBB.
While it <i>does</i> mean a lot of chaos for the next little while, as folks get
their registrations set up, etc., if board traffic stays relatively stable, it
will cost us about 25% of what our Gold renewal would cost. I suspect that the
actual numbers may be closer to 50% if the current growth curve continues, but
it's still a hefty amount of money.
<p>I fully realize this means everyone needs to register for yet another message
board, and re-do your preferences for sigs, etc. It will also mean that custom
posting titles will be pretty much MIA for the time being, and that those of you
who earned titles due to post count tallies may not be happy about having to
re-earn titles all over again. Much as I am sorry for the extra chaos this
causes for everyone, better that chaos than a) ads all over the place, or b) me
deciding this is costing too much time and money and throwing in the towel.
(Really, I don't want to do 'b'. I very much don't want to do that, and I've
turned down some very blunt cash offers for the site ownership recently. I will
not do that to this community ... but I am <i>very</i> burnt out IRL, and I'm
very much dreading the hubub that's going to hit once I publish this front page
update ...) Bleargh.
<p>Anywayyyy ... I'm leaving the old boards up for now, but nudging you all to <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/index.php">use
the new boards</a>. I'll leave the old links in place for a bit longer, so folks
can copy over any needed information from server forums, etc. into the new ones.
In another week (or less if it gets too crazed handling both sets of boards),
I'll block posting to the old boards, but leave them up for reference purposes.
</p>
<p>
